title: Sports Roundup: Hendrix and Greenbrier volleyball; UCA women's soccer
text:
Sports Roundup: Hendrix and Greenbrier volleyball; UCA women's soccer Posted: October 5, 2015 - 8:30pm LOG CABIN DEMOCRAT 
ATLANTA - The Hendrix College volleyball team completed the first round of Southern Athletic Association play undefeated after sweeping Oglethorpe University on the road Sunday. 
With the 25-19, 26-24, 25-15 win, the Warriors moved to 13-6 overall and 7-0 in conference play. The Stormy Petrels fell to 4-14 and 0-7. 
Lauren Petrisin led the Warriors with a season-high 15 kills and hit .385. UCA WOMEN’S SOCCER 
ABILENE, TEXAS — Maria Gomez’ goal off a free kick with 37 left n the first half gave Abilene Christian (4-7-2l 3-1-1) a 1-0 victory on Sunday against the University of Central Arkansas women’s soccer team (6-7, 3-2). 
Central Arkansas managed just one shot in the second half. GREENBRIER VOLLEYBALL 
Greenbrier’s volleyball team upped its conferencer record to 7-2 last week with a 25-16, 25-8, 25-16 victory over Maumelle. 
Katherine Jeane had 16 kills. Christina Curtis was a defensive leader. Jaylee Engelkes had 16 kills. 
Greenbrier won the JV match, 25-13, 25-14. Hollis Redden had 18 assists, Madison Matyja, eight kills, Natalie Burns, five kills and six aces . Andie Finley was a defensive leader. 
Greenbrier (16-5) defeated Clarksville, 25-17, 25-13, 25-16. Leaders were Kobie Hartman, 21 assists, four aces; Jeane, 12 kills; Harlie Langston, 13 kills; and Curtis. 
Greenbrier won the JV match, 25-7, 25-15. Redden had 10 assists, Matyja, five aces, and Payton Miller, six kills.
